mindset to solve problems.

145
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,240
What is TCM mindset?

146
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,320
We employ teaching
through clinical practice.

147
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,480
So, I believe

148
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,280
teacher-apprentice education

149
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:57,840
in TCM

150
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,120
will return.

151
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,160
If a student cannot learn well,

152
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:03,600
then the problem must lie
with the teaching method.

153
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,960
If a student isn't taught well,

154
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,560
it must be the fault of his master.

155
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,080
Your takeout is here!

156
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,400
Pick up the phone.

157
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,200
I will leave it at the door.

158
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:35,840
Help! Help!

159
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,000
Open the door!

160
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:40,800
Open it!

161
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:42,680
Open it!

162
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:43,800
Open it!

163
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,120
Sorry, teachers. I'm probably late.

164
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,960
You are not late.

165
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,160
You are just in time.

166
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,240
Thank you.

167
00:08:58,680 --> 00:08:59,680
I'm sorry, sir.

168
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,040
What is

169
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:08,160
the emergency first aid
for an open fracture?

170
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,240
The emergency...

171
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:12,000
The emergency first aid
for an open fracture...

172
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:20,600
-Do you still want it or not?
-No.

173
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:21,800
Fine. Take this!

174
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,120
Relax. Relax.

175
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,560
It's not a difficult question.

176
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,040
Don't be nervous.

177
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,040
I'm not nervous. I'm angry!

178
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,360
Sorry about that.

179
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:38,480
Can you repeat the question?

180
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,480
Sorry.

181
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,360
What is

182
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:47,440
the emergency first aid
for an open fracture?

183
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:54,920
Please tell us the emergency treatment
methods for an open fracture.

184
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:03,600
Help me.

185
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:04,720
Come back here!

186
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:06,680
The first step in the emergency
treatment of an open fracture

187
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,440
is to perform life-saving measures.

188
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:09,680
We should quickly conduct

189
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,240
a comprehensive examination
of the patient.

190
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:14,360
If a cardiac arrest occurs,
perform a CPR immediately.

191
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,160
Next is to apply dressing
and stop the bleeding.

192
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,880
It is important to use clean clothing
for bandaging the wound.

193
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,520
The exposed fractured ends

194
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,640
should not be pulled back
into the skin tissue

195
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:23,720
to avoid potential misdiagnosis
by medical professionals.

196
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,280
Thirdly, temporary splinting is required.

197
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,760
It is important to use
rigid objects for splinting.

198
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,000
The splint

199
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,240
should extend beyond the fractured
area by one joint above and below.

200
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,040
Without proper splinting,

201
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:34,520
the patient or injured limb
should not be moved arbitrarily.

202
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,520
Let go!

203
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,360
Stop fighting!

204
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,400
Stop it!

205
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,520
Stop!

206
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,680
These are my answers.

207
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:10,800
Thank you.

208
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,000
Thank you.

209
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:37,280
Ouch.

210
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,360
Be gentle.

211
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:40,680
Thank you.

212
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:41,960
Why did she hit you?

213
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,320
We didn't give her a good rating.

214
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,800
You hit them just because they
didn't give you a good rating?

215
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:09,560
Are you sure that's the truth?

216
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,440
Madam,

217
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,360
Master.

218
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:42,120
Master, madam,

219
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,680
I have an idea.

220
00:12:44,520 --> 00:12:46,160
I don't know if it will work.

221
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:49,160
I'd like to organize
a TCM apprentice class.

222
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:53,160
What is teacher-student succession?

223
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,520
How do you want to do it?

224
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:55,880
I will follow the example
of the ancients,

225
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:57,040
with teachers guiding students,

226
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:58,880
let education fosters mutual growth.

227
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,360
Talking about this

228
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:03,440
is easy in theory.

229
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,200
But how are you going
to put it into practice?

230
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,720
It's easy to find a teacher.

231
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:09,320
Over the years,

232
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,240
you've searched for many TCM doctors,

233
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:12,280
and you've got the ability.

234
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:14,000
But what about the apprentices?

235
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:17,480
Are you going to recruit
student from the medical school?

236
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:18,560
Besides,

237
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,280
by doing this, you are
going against the school

238
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,480
and setting up a new school.

239
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:23,520
Madam,

240
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:26,080
the 52nd decree of the Ministry of Health

241
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:27,360
explicitly stipulates

242
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:28,840
that any student

243
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:30,520
who aspires to learn TCM,

244
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:33,680
with a high school diploma
or equivalent education,

245
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:36,600
can obtain a medical
practice qualification

246
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:37,920
by continuously apprenticing

247
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,600
with a master for three years

248
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:41,640
and passing the medical
licensing examination.

249
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:42,840
Actually, I think

250
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:45,000
the philosophy of TCM is about harmony

251
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:46,920
and assistance,

252
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:48,360
not resistance.

253
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:51,360
That's an interesting idea

254
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,120
you've got there.

255
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:54,920
Easy there.

256
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:58,680
Please explain clearly
what you mean by "lecturing" first.

257
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,360
I want to conduct an open lecture.

258
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:01,680
An inclusive education.

259
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:03,120
Spread the knowledge of TCM.

260
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,320
Spread it?

261
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,400
Yes.

262
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:08,360
TCM is not Confucianism.

263
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:10,960
You can't recruit thousands
of disciples like Confucius.

264
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:13,160
TCM has existed for thousands of years.

265
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:15,680
The greatest fear is that it will
be passed on to the wrong people.

266
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:16,960
It will ruin its spirit.

267
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:18,240
And you want to pass on
the knowledge to more people,

268
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:20,360
if someone with ill intentions

269
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,040
uses these knowledge

270
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,240
for wrongdoing

271
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:24,680
and gains unjust gains,

272
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:25,920
what should we do then?

273
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:27,120
Madam,

274
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:28,720
integrity

275
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,120
is the way of nature.

276
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:33,080
The principle of nature is to be
honest and never deceive.

277
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:36,120
As long as a person
possesses integrity and honesty,

278
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:38,440
they will not betray
the precious knowledge of TCM.

279
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,680
